---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Insights — Growth Research for HVAC, Roofing & Plumbing | Built on Tenth"
  description="Research, benchmarks, and analysis from studying hundreds of home service companies. What the most profitable HVAC, roofing, and plumbing operators do differently."
  active="insights"
>

<style>
.insights-hero { padding: 140px 48px 80px; position: relative; overflow: hidden; }
.insights-hero-glow { position: absolute; inset: 0; background: radial-gradient(ellipse 60% 60% at 20% 50%, rgba(0,196,154,0.05) 0%, transparent 60%); }
.insights-hero-inner { position: relative; z-index: 1; max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 80px; align-items: end; }
.insights-hero h1 { font-family: var(--serif); font-size: clamp(38px, 5vw, 60px); font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.1; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 22px; }
.insights-hero h1 em { font-style: italic; color: var(--teal); }

/* Pillar tabs */
.pillar-tabs { display: flex; gap: 8px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
.pt {
  font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 10px; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--ink3); background: var(--bg3); border: 1px solid var(--rule2);
  padding: 7px 14px; border-radius: 3px; cursor: pointer; text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.2s;
}
.pt:hover, .pt.active { color: var(--teal); border-color: var(--teal4); background: var(--teal3); }

/* Coming soon / placeholder article grid */
.articles-grid {
  display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  gap: 1px; background: var(--rule); border: 1px solid var(--rule);
  border-radius: 6px; overflow: hidden; margin-top: 48px;
}
.article-card { background: var(--bg2); padding: 32px 28px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; transition: background 0.25s; }
.article-card:hover { background: var(--bg3); }
.article-card.placeholder { opacity: 0.5; }
.article-trade { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9.5px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--teal); margin-bottom: 14px; }
.article-title { font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 19px; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.3; margin-bottom: 12px; flex: 1; }
.article-preview { font-size: 13.5px; color: var(--ink2); line-height: 1.65; font-weight: 300; margin-bottom: 18px; }
.article-meta { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; }
.article-date { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 10px; color: var(--ink3); letter-spacing: 0.06em; }
.article-read { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 10px; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--teal); text-decoration: none; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 5px; transition: gap 0.2s; }
.article-card:hover .article-read { gap: 8px; }

/* Coming soon banner */
.coming-soon-banner {
  background: var(--bg3); border: 1px solid var(--rule2); border-radius: 6px;
  padding: 48px; text-align: center; margin-top: 1px;
}
.csb-icon { font-size: 32px; margin-bottom: 16px; }
.csb-h { font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 24px; font-weight: 400; margin-bottom: 10px; }
.csb-p { font-size: 14px; color: var(--ink2); line-height: 1.7; font-weight: 300; max-width: 480px; margin: 0 auto 24px; }

/* Newsletter CTA */
.nl-prompt { background: var(--bg2); border: 1px solid rgba(0,196,154,0.25); border-radius: 6px; padding: 32px 36px; margin-top: 48px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; gap: 24px; }
.nl-prompt-text h3 { font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 20px; font-weight: 400; margin-bottom: 6px; }
.nl-prompt-text p { font-size: 13.5px; color: var(--ink2); font-weight: 300; line-height: 1.6; }
.nl-prompt-form { display: flex; gap: 10px; flex-shrink: 0; }
.nl-prompt-input { background: var(--bg3); border: 1px solid var(--rule2); border-radius: 4px; padding: 11px 16px; font-family: var(--sans); font-size: 13.5px; color: var(--ink); outline: none; transition: border-color 0.2s; width: 220px; }
.nl-prompt-input::placeholder { color: var(--ink3); }
.nl-prompt-input:focus { border-color: rgba(0,196,154,0.5); }

@media (max-width: 960px) {
  .insights-hero { padding: 120px 20px 72px; }
  .insights-hero-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 32px; }
  .articles-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .nl-prompt { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; }
  .nl-prompt-form { flex-direction: column; width: 100%; }
  .nl-prompt-input { width: 100%; }
}
</style>

<div class="insights-hero">
  <div class="insights-hero-glow"></div>
  <div class="insights-hero-inner">
    <div>
      <div class="dispatch-label">Research &amp; Analysis</div>
      <h1>What the most profitable companies<br><em>actually do differently.</em></h1>
      <p class="sec-p">Every article is built on data from analyzing real HVAC, roofing, and plumbing companies — their ad spend, phone systems, close rates, and competitive positioning. No opinion pieces. No generic advice. Just patterns from the data.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <p style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--ink3);margin-bottom:14px">Filter by trade</p>
      <div class="pillar-tabs">
        <a href="/insights" class="pt active">All</a>
        <a href="/insights?trade=HVAC" class="pt">HVAC</a>
        <a href="/insights?trade=Roofing" class="pt">Roofing</a>
        <a href="/insights?trade=Plumbing" class="pt">Plumbing</a>
        <a href="/insights?topic=phone" class="pt">Phone Systems</a>
        <a href="/insights?topic=google" class="pt">Google Ads</a>
        <a href="/insights?topic=gbp" class="pt">Google Business</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="wrap">
  <div class="inner">
    <div class="rule-label"><span class="section-tag">Research</span></div>

    <!-- Published articles will render here — placeholder shows the structure -->
    <div class="articles-grid">
      <div class="article-card reveal">
        <div class="article-trade">HVAC · Google Ads</div>
        <div class="article-title">What It Actually Costs to Book One HVAC Job From Google Ads in 2025</div>
        <p class="article-preview">We analyzed 87 HVAC companies' Google Ads accounts and their booking data. The average cost per booked job is $340 — but the top 25% are paying $110. Here's what separates them.</p>
        <div class="article-meta">
          <span class="article-date">Coming soon</span>
          <span class="article-read">Read →</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="article-card reveal">
        <div class="article-trade">All Trades · Phone Systems</div>
        <div class="article-title">HVAC Phone Answer Rate Benchmarks — What the Top 25% Do Differently</div>
        <p class="article-preview">The national average answer rate for home service companies is 66%. The top quartile answers 89% of calls. Here's exactly what systems they have in place and what the gap costs.</p>
        <div class="article-meta">
          <span class="article-date">Coming soon</span>
          <span class="article-read">Read →</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="article-card reveal">
        <div class="article-trade">Roofing · Lead Sources</div>
        <div class="article-title">Why Angi Leads Feel Like Garbage (And What Roofing Companies Do Instead)</div>
        <p class="article-preview">Angi leads have a 12–18% close rate industry-wide — but some roofing companies close 35% of them. The difference isn't the lead quality. It's what happens in the first 4 minutes after the call comes in.</p>
        <div class="article-meta">
          <span class="article-date">Coming soon</span>
          <span class="article-read">Read →</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="coming-soon-banner">
      <div class="csb-icon">📊</div>
      <div class="csb-h">New research drops every week.</div>
      <p class="csb-p">We publish 2 articles a week — real data, specific dollar amounts, contractor language. Subscribe to the newsletter and we'll send each one the day it goes live.</p>
      <a href="/newsletter" class="cta-primary">Get New Research Every Tuesday →</a>
    </div>

    <!-- Newsletter inline prompt -->
    <div class="nl-prompt">
      <div class="nl-prompt-text">
        <h3>Get every article before it's indexed.</h3>
        <p>Subscribe to the Weekly Growth Report. One insight every Tuesday. Free.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="nl-prompt-form">
        <input type="email" class="nl-prompt-input" placeholder="your@email.com" id="insights-email" />
        <button class="cta-filled" style="cursor:pointer" id="insights-submit">Subscribe</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<script>
  document.getElementById('insights-submit').addEventListener('click', () => {
    const inp = document.getElementById('insights-email');
    if (inp.value.includes('@')) {
      document.getElementById('insights-submit').textContent = '✓ Subscribed';
      document.getElementById('insights-submit').style.background = '#22D37A';
      inp.disabled = true;
    } else {
      inp.style.borderColor = 'rgba(240,64,64,0.55)';
      inp.focus();
    }
  });
</script>
</Layout>
